This paper is about differential privacy in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with privacy concerns in training machine learning models. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper proposes a privacy-preserving mechanism for sharing sensitive data. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the use of ensembles and voting procedures in differential privacy. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new framework for training machine learning models. The fifth likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with the trade-off between privacy and performance in machine learning models.
